channel.description: hi i have 2 jdks and that is 7 and 11 and i dont think i can compile is it a problem with that or my envoirment variables and in envoirment variables theres a top bit (classpath) and bottom bit (path) in the bottom bit there is also classpath is that allright? thanks

item.title: What happens when u have 2 jdk's
item.dc:creator: @adamp40 adamp40
item.description:
@adamp40 wrote:

Nothing happens when you have 2 jdk versions.

As long as the Value of your Path is
C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_11\bin;

You should be OK.
